Parliament, Monday, 30 July 2018 –  The Select Committee on Social Services will this week undertake an oversight programme in the Free State province to assess progress in implementation of commitments made by the Provincial Department of Health during the 2017 Taking Parliament to the People (TPTTP) programme in the province. The Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces, Ms Thandi Modise made a pledge during the TPTTP programme that the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will continue to monitor progress in the implementation of interventions to ensure that the people of the province receive quality healthcare. “This visit is the realisation of that promise made by the Chairperson that the NCOP will continue to do follow-up visits to ensure that commitments are translated into real action on the ground,” said Mrs Cathy Dlamini, the Chairperson of the committee. The committee will visit various healthcare sites to see first-hand if indeed interventions have been implemented. On the First day the committee will visit the Gariep Dam Clinic, Fauresmith Clinic and the Albert Nzula Hospital. Details of the 1st Day visit are as follows Date: Tuesday, 31 July 2018 
	Venue: Gariep Dam Clinic 
	Time: 09:30 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON SOCIAL SERVICES, MRS CATHY DLAMINI For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
